RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLDBRIDGE settled in behind to track saving ground through the first turn, moved out while advancing on the leader on the far turn coming up to that one three wide, struck the lead outside the eighth pole, inched away and was kept to the task. TREASURE COAST set the pace racing off the rail into the first turn, was pressured leaving that bend and up the backstretch before edging clear before the far turn, was challenged at the top of the stretch, overtaken, kept on willingly but was no match for the winner while second best. STAPLETON SONG rated in behind the leaders racing off the inside, moved out four wide coming to the quarter pole and gaining to within striking distance but could not sustain the effort and flattened out. CLINTON QUARINTINO stalked from outside racing mostly three to four wide, failed to rally. BARN SHARK pressed the pace outside three wide, came up empty.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: EURO TRACKING bobbled slightly at the start but went forward to set the pace racing off the rail, faced pressure from an inside rival, dispatched that foe then faced pressure from an outside rival late on the turn, turned back that one and kicked clear. FORT NECESSITY moved up inside heading to the turn, shifted out to go three wide on that bend, drew along the flank of the eventual winner but was no match. SWORD OF GOLD raced near the inside off the pace and improved position. ROWDY GALE was off the inside part of the track and needed more. TOMMY TSUNAMI stalked from outside four wide, weakened. MISTER TYRO was encouraged forward, pressed the winner from inside, came up empty. HORNS DOWN was reluctant to load, got away slowly, lacked early speed, lost the irons at some point and was distanced, crossed the wire and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 21000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RAINBOWS ARE FREE tracked in behind racing off the rail, moved out to commence a rally four then five wide on the far turn, struck the lead outside the three-sixteenths, drifted in a tad in upper stretch and edged clear under steady handling. NORDIC QUEEN vied two to three wide between runners, dueled inside a rival but off the fence drifting out a bit turning for home, was overtaken in upper stretch but kept on to preserve the place. SPELL FREEDOM contended outside three to four wide, was carried out a bit leaving the far turn and in a bit tight in upper stretch while beginning to weaken, lacked the needed late kick. TOSH settled inside, came off the rail and passed tired rivals. MISS ARKANSAS was strongly urged at the break but lacking speed, raced several paths removed from the rail, advanced some on the far turn but faded thereafter. SPLITSECONDECISION was in range early pursuing from outside four to five wide, moved out further on the far turn and weakened. MISS CARMEN CIBO prompted the pace from inside the opening three furlongs, steadily weakened. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF SPELL FREEDOM AGAINST NORDIC QUEEN ALLEGING INTERFERENCE NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
